Error Type	               Compile?	     Run?
Syntax Error	           ❌	        ❌
Compilation Error	       ❌	        ❌
Logical Error	           ✅	        ✅ (wrong output)
Runtime Error	           ✅	        ❌
Index Out of Bounds	       ✅	        ⚠️ Undefined behavior
Infinite Loop	           ✅	        ⚠️ Never ends
Concurrency Issue	       ✅	        ⚠️ Wrong results
I/O Error	               ✅	        ⚠️ File operation fails
Environment Dependency	   ✅	        ⚠️ Platform-specific failure
Integration Error	       ❌/⚠️	        ❌/⚠️
Reference Error	           ✅	        ⚠️ Undefined behavior
Type Error	               ❌	        ❌

SEMANTIC Error = Same to the syntax error but A syntax error is a violation of the grammatical rules of a programming language, while a semantic error occurs when the code is grammatically correct but performs an operation that makes no sense or is impossible to execute.
LINK ERROR = Something externally isn't found like a Reference